# Data Models

This rule describes the database schema and data relationships in the Alt Regioni project. The project uses Prisma ORM with a SQL database.

## Core Models

### User

Users of the application.

```prisma
model User {
  id            String    @id @default(cuid())
  name          String?
  email         String?   @unique
  emailVerified DateTime?
  image         String?
  accounts      Account[]
  sessions      Session[]
  members       Member[]
  invitations   Invitation[]
}
```

### Organization

Organizations that users can be part of.

```prisma
model Organization {
  id          String      @id @default(cuid())
  name        String
  slug        String      @unique
  logo        String?
  metadata    Json?
  members     Member[]
  invitations Invitation[]
  forms       Form[]
  files       File[]
  folders     FileFolder[]
  reviewFlows ReviewFlow[]
}
```

### Member

Represents a user's membership in an organization with a specific role.

```prisma
model Member {
  id             String     @id @default(cuid())
  organizationId String
  userId         String
  role           MemberRole @default(member)
  organization   Organization @relation(fields: [organizationId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  user           User       @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  createdForms   Form[]     @relation("FormCreator")
  assignedForms  Form[]     @relation("FormExecutor")
  comments       Comment[]
  formHistory    FormHistory[]
  uploadedFiles  File[]
  sharedFiles    FileShare[]
  createdFolders FileFolder[]
}

enum MemberRole {
  owner
  admin
  reviewer
  executor
  member
}
```

### Form

Forms that can be created, filled, and reviewed.

```prisma
model Form {
  id               String     @id @default(cuid())
  organizationId   String
  creatorMemberId  String
  executorMemberId String?
  templateId       String?
  reviewFlowId     String?
  title            String
  description      String?
  status           FormStatus @default(DRAFT)
  version          Int        @default(1)
  organization     Organization @relation(fields: [organizationId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  creator          Member     @relation("FormCreator", fields: [creatorMemberId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  executor         Member?    @relation("FormExecutor", fields: [executorMemberId], references: [id])
  template         FormTemplate? @relation(fields: [templateId], references: [id])
  reviewFlow       ReviewFlow? @relation(fields: [reviewFlowId], references: [id])
  fields           FormField[]
  history          FormHistory[]
}

enum FormStatus {
  DRAFT
  UNDER_REVIEW
  NEEDS_CHANGES
  APPROVED
  REJECTED
}
```

### File

Files uploaded to the system.

```prisma
model File {
  id             String     @id @default(cuid())
  organizationId String
  uploaderId     String
  folderId       String?
  filename       String
  originalName   String
  path           String
  mimeType       String
  size           Int
  accessLevel    FileAccess @default(ORGANIZATION)
  version        Int        @default(1)
  lastModifiedAt DateTime   @default(now())
  organization   Organization @relation(fields: [organizationId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  uploader       Member     @relation(fields: [uploaderId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  folder         FileFolder? @relation(fields: [folderId], references: [id])
  formFields     FormFieldFile[]
  sharedWith     FileShare[]
}

enum FileAccess {
  PRIVATE
  ORGANIZATION
  PUBLIC
}
```

## Supporting Models

### FormField

Fields within a form.

```prisma
model FormField {
  id           String    @id @default(cuid())
  formId       String
  templateFieldId String?
  label        String
  type         FieldType
  required     Boolean   @default(false)
  order        Int
  options      Json?
  value        String?
  form         Form      @relation(fields: [formId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  templateField FormTemplateField? @relation(fields: [templateFieldId], references: [id])
  files        FormFieldFile[]
}

enum FieldType {
  TEXT
  TEXTAREA
  NUMBER
  DATE
  SELECT
  CHECKBOX
  RADIO
  FILE
}
```

### FormTemplate

Templates for creating standardized forms.

```prisma
model FormTemplate {
  id           String    @id @default(cuid())
  title        String
  description  String?
  fields       FormTemplateField[]
  forms        Form[]
}
```

### FileFolder

Hierarchical folder structure for files.

```prisma
model FileFolder {
  id             String     @id @default(cuid())
  organizationId String
  creatorId      String
  parentId       String?
  name           String
  path           String
  version        Int        @default(1)
  lastModifiedAt DateTime   @default(now())
  organization   Organization @relation(fields: [organizationId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  creator        Member     @relation(fields: [creatorId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  parent         FileFolder? @relation("FolderHierarchy", fields: [parentId], references: [id])
  children       FileFolder[] @relation("FolderHierarchy")
  files          File[]
}
```

### ReviewFlow

Represents a review process for forms.

```prisma
model ReviewFlow {
  id             String           @id @default(cuid())
  organizationId String
  title          String
  description    String?
  status         ReviewFlowStatus @default(OPEN)
  organization   Organization     @relation(fields: [organizationId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  forms          Form[]
  comments       Comment[]
}

enum ReviewFlowStatus {
  OPEN
  CLOSED
}
```

## Relationships Overview

1. **User to Organization** (Many-to-Many)
   - A user can be a member of multiple organizations
   - An organization can have multiple users as members
   - The Member model serves as the join table with additional role information

2. **Organization to Form** (One-to-Many)
   - An organization can have multiple forms
   - Each form belongs to a single organization

3. **Form to FormField** (One-to-Many)
   - A form can have multiple fields
   - Each field belongs to a single form

4. **Organization to File** (One-to-Many)
   - An organization can have multiple files
   - Each file belongs to a single organization

5. **FileFolder Hierarchy** (Self-Relation)
   - A folder can have a parent folder
   - A folder can have multiple child folders

6. **Form to ReviewFlow** (Many-to-One)
   - Multiple forms can be part of a single review flow
   - Each form can have at most one review flow

## Permission System

The permission system is built around the Member model's role field:

- **owner**: Full access to the organization
- **admin**: Administrative access to manage the organization
- **reviewer**: Can review forms and provide feedback
- **executor**: Can fill out assigned forms
- **member**: Basic access to organization resources

File permissions are controlled through the accessLevel field:

- **PRIVATE**: Only accessible to the uploader
- **ORGANIZATION**: Accessible to all members of the organization
- **PUBLIC**: Accessible to anyone with the link

## Data Access Patterns

1. **Organization-Scoped Data**: Most queries filter by organizationId
2. **Role-Based Access**: Permissions are checked based on the user's role in the organization
3. **Version Control**: Forms, folders, and files track version numbers
4. **Hierarchical Data**: Folders support parent-child relationships
